A Chief Magistrates’ Court in Ebute Meta, Lagos State on Friday ordered that an officer of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Oluwafemi Emmanuel, 42, who allegedly stabbed a police inspector to death, be remanded in a correctional facility. Emmanuel is charged with homicide. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs F.M Kayode-Alamu, did not take the plea of Emmanuel. Kayode-Alamu ordered that Emmanuel be remanded in Ikoyi Custodial Centre, pending legal advice. She adjourned the case until Aug. 10. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel., Insp Olatunde Kehinde alleged that Emmanuel committed the offence on May 24, at No. 10, Okotie Eboh St., Ikoyi. He also alleged that Emmanuel used a Jack-knife and stabbed Insp. Edward Ngbekem in the chest during a disagreement. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of Section 223 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, which prescribes a death sentence for convict. (NAN) Lagos -  The police on Friday in Lagos, arraigned one Ridwan Lukuman,21, alleged to be a cultist, in an Ebute Metta Chief Magistrates' Court, for allegedly stabbing one Kazeem Taiwo to death. Lukuman is standing trial on charges bordering on conspiracy, murder and belonging to a cult. The court, however,… April 17, 2015 In "News" LAGOS - An Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates' Court in Lagos on Tuesday remanded in prison a man, Musibau Sulaimon, who allegedly stole N14, 000 from one Francis Chukwuemeka and stabbed him with a dagger. The accused, a labourer from Ayetoro in Ogun, was arraigned on a three-count charge of conspiracy,… February 17, 2015 In "News" By Teniola Ibitola Lagos   -     A Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps personnel, Kehinde Osho, who allegedly shot and killed a man, on Friday appeared before an Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Osho, whose address was not provided, is facing a count charge of murder, but he pleaded… January 4, 2019 In "Metro"